cerent454Mib.description: The is the node under which all Cisco ONS 15454 specific mib object are located.

cerent454Conformance.description: This node is created compliance. Has objects as required by the RFCs

cerentCommonObjects.name: cerentCommonObjects
cerentCommonObjects.description: The objects here are expected to be used by all Cisco OTBU Products. These will be mixed with specific objects of the product-specific branch.

cerentCommonEvents.name: cerentCommonEvents
cerentCommonEvents.description: This branch is similar to cerentCommonObjects, except that this will have only events

Cerent454AlarmType.description: This TC is used by the NMS to map the alarm type received by the trap and and display the string shown in LHS.

Cerent454EntityClass.name: Cerent454EntityClass
Cerent454EntityClass.description: This is the TC used to find out to which cerent454EntityClass an alarm belongs to.

cerent454CommonObjectsGroup.name: cerent454CommonObjectsGroup
cerent454CommonObjectsGroup.description: The group to combine all the Cisco OTBU common objects

cerent454EnableNotification.name: cerent454EnableNotification
cerent454EnableNotification.description: This variable indicates whether the system produces notifications. A value=FALSE will prevent notifications from being sent by this system.

cerent454NodeTime.name: cerent454NodeTime
cerent454NodeTime.description: Indicates current local time as reflected by the Cisco OTBU equipment. The format this scalar is YYYYMMDDhhmmss{S/D}. E.g., 20011103133453D means 1:34:53 PM PDT on 03/Nov/2001 19990614095436S means 9:54:36 AM PST on 14/Jun/1999. If the last octet is S then the time is standard time. Otherwise it is D to indicate it is daylight saving time, if applicable

cerent454SentNotifications.name: cerent454SentNotifications
cerent454SentNotifications.description: A count of v1+v2 notifications sent out by the agent. Resets to zero after cold/warm start.

cerent454LastChangeTime.name: cerent454LastChangeTime
cerent454LastChangeTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time a conceptual row is created or deleted in cerent454AlarmTable

cerent454MultishelfEnabled.name: cerent454MultishelfEnabled
cerent454MultishelfEnabled.description: This variable indicates whether the system is configured in multi-shelf mode or single-shelf mode.

cerent454SoftwareVersion.name: cerent454SoftwareVersion
cerent454SoftwareVersion.description: Indicates the version of software that is used in Cisco ONS 15454. E.g., 2.2.03

cerent454AlarmGroup.name: cerent454AlarmGroup
cerent454AlarmGroup.description: The group that will represent all the alarm info in the Cisco ONS 15454 node

cerent454AlarmCount.name: cerent454AlarmCount
cerent454AlarmCount.description: Total number of active alarms in Cisco ONS 15454. This equals the total number of rows in cerent454AlarmTable at any time.

cerent454AlarmTable.name: cerent454AlarmTable
cerent454AlarmTable.description: This table has all currently raised conditions for the network node. A Condition is a fault or status detected by hardware or software.

cerent454AlarmIndex.name: cerent454AlarmIndex
cerent454AlarmIndex.description: Identifies each entry in alarm table. May not start with one and there may be some missing numbers.

cerent454AlarmObjectType.name: cerent454AlarmObjectType
cerent454AlarmObjectType.description: This will indicate what is the type of the entity which raised this alarm. ( E.g., DS3, etherBridge, VT-TERM, etc ) The NMS is expected to use this value to decide which table to poll for further info about the alarm

cerent454AlarmSlotNumber.name: cerent454AlarmSlotNumber
cerent454AlarmSlotNumber.description: This will indicate what is the slot of the object which raised this alarm. If not relevant to the alarm, will be zero.

cerent454AlarmPortNumber.name: cerent454AlarmPortNumber
cerent454AlarmPortNumber.description: This will indicate what is the port of the object which raised this alarm.

cerent454AlarmLineNumber.name: cerent454AlarmLineNumber
cerent454AlarmLineNumber.description: This will indicate what is the port of the object which raised this alarm. If not relevant to the alarm, will be zero.

cerent454AlarmObjectIndex.name: cerent454AlarmObjectIndex
cerent454AlarmObjectIndex.description: Every alarm is raised by an object and this object is an entry in a specific table. This is the index of the object in that table E.g., if the alarm is interface related, this index is the index of the interface in the interface table.

cerent454AlarmType.name: cerent454AlarmType
cerent454AlarmType.description: Indicates what the exact nature of the alarm. See the Cerent454AlarmType TC for mapping details

cerent454AlarmState.name: cerent454AlarmState
cerent454AlarmState.description: Specifies alarm severity and service affecting status ( SA/NSA ). Only {minor|major|critical}+{NA|NSA} alarms and standing conditions will be represented here. However, this mib object is included in each trap dispatched and in the trap this object can contain all the possible values of CerentNotificationClass type.

cerent454AlarmTimeStamp.name: cerent454AlarmTimeStamp
cerent454AlarmTimeStamp.description: The value of sysUpTime when this entry was created. This is accurate only upto a second.

cerent454AlarmObjectName.name: cerent454AlarmObjectName
cerent454AlarmObjectName.description: TL1-style user-visible name which uniquely identifies an object in the system

cerent454AlarmAdditionalInfo.name: cerent454AlarmAdditionalInfo
cerent454AlarmAdditionalInfo.description: Additional information for the alarm object. In the current version of the MIB, this object contains the following information :- a) Provisioned description for alarms of type 'failureDetectedExternalToTheNE'. This object would be a null string if no additional information is specified.

cerent454AlarmSeverity.name: cerent454AlarmSeverity
cerent454AlarmSeverity.description: Specifies severity of the alarm being sent out.

cerent454AlarmStatus.name: cerent454AlarmStatus
cerent454AlarmStatus.description: Represents if the alarm is currently raised or cleared.

cerent454AlarmServiceAffecting.name: cerent454AlarmServiceAffecting
cerent454AlarmServiceAffecting.description: Specifies whether the alarm that is being sent out is Service Affecting (SA) or Non- Service Affecting (NSA).

cerent454ReportedAlarmCount.name: cerent454ReportedAlarmCount
cerent454ReportedAlarmCount.description: Number of alarms currently reported against Cisco ONS 15454. This equals the number of rows in cerent454ReportedAlarmTable.

cerent454ReportedAlarmTable.name: cerent454ReportedAlarmTable
cerent454ReportedAlarmTable.description: This table has the list of alarms currently reported for the Cisco ONS node. It does not include any cleared alarms. The alarms in this table are in compliance with Telcordia GR-253. This means that if a network problem causes two alarms, such a as loss of frame(LOF) and loss of signal(LOS), only LOS alarm will be in this table because it supersedes and replaces the LOF.
